   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <l>I Hang no Iuie out to sell my Wine,</l>
   <l>The <hi>Nectar</hi> of good witts will sell it selfe;</l>
   <l>I feare not, what detraction can define,</l>
   <l>I saile secure from <hi>Enuies</hi> storme or shelfe.</l>
   <l>I set my picture out to each mans vewe,</l>
   <l>Limd with these colours, and so cunning arts,</l>
   <l>That like the <hi>Phaenix</hi> will their age renewe,</l>
   <l>And conquer <hi>Enuie</hi> by their good desarts.</l>
   <l>If any Cobler carpe aboue his shoo,</l>
   <l>I rather pittie, then repine his action,</l>
   <l>For ignorance stil maketh much adoo,</l>
   <l>And wisdom loues that, which offēds detrac<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tion.</l>
   <l>Go fearles forth my booke, hate cānot harm thee,</l>
   <l>
      <hi>Apollo</hi> bred thee, &amp; the <hi>Muses</hi> arm thee.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>R. A.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
